HEADWORD: Engregge
<hw>En*greg"ge</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>engregier</ets>, from (assumed) LL. <ets>ingreviare</ets>;
<ets>in</ets> + (assumed) <ets>grevis</ets> heavy, for L.
<ets>gravis</ets>. Cf. <er>Aggravate</er>.]</ety> <def>To aggravate; to
make worse; to lie heavy on.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

